<!-- The enforcer pattern is language-agnostic; only the runner changes:
     Node: scripts/ci/<name>.mjs   Go: a *_test.go or go vet check
     Rust: cargo clippy / cargo xtask   Python: ruff / a pytest check
     Whatever the runner, the gate must assert a REAL outcome (a count, a value,
     non-emptiness), fail-closed on "no tests collected," and keep its own config
     un-editable in the same turn it is checked. -->
